metadata.name: Departure Within Shattered Windmills #100
metadata.description:
I wrote the following when reviewing the outputs...

The wind is gone,
My windmill falls,
I reach out to catch the pieces.
Half fall in my right hand,
The others in my left,
Two stacks of colored paper.
Iâ€™m holding my windmill,
I feel the breeze in my hair.
Each hand is empty,
My windmill rises,
I can see the wind.

'Departure Within Shattered Windmills' was originally inspired by suprematism, and then started to gain more complexity. It is still a combination of simple features, subdivided quads drawn on different planes of perspective. Chaos simulated by many organized grids. Countless pieces of a windmill.

25% of the royalties for each edition will pass to the original minter.

Each output is generated from code written in p5js.

Created by Eric Davidson. 2022.

metadata.name: Naive Nature #9
metadata.description:
A Generative Landscape with AI-Generated Surprises

This generative artwork in naive style made with AI was edited by a human. The code uses various random functions to generate a landscape scene with mountains, clouds, trees, and grass. The color palette is also chosen randomly from a set of predefined palettes.

The code includes conditional statements that allow for the inclusion of a sun or moon, as well as an AI-generated car or face. If a car is generated, it is placed randomly on the canvas and consists of four rectangles of various sizes and colors. If a face is generated, it is scaled down and translated to the upper left corner of the canvas, and consists of a blue rectangular head, two white circular eyes with black pupils, a curved mouth, and a simple antenna.

The final output is a unique artwork that is both generated by AI and edited by a human, resulting in a delightful mix of randomness and intentionality.

metadata.name: Kinetograms #195
metadata.description:
Each Kinetogram traces the movement of a number of simple shapes constrained within a single cell or a grid of cells. Forces are applied to the shapes in the form of attraction, gravity or shaking.

Some Kinetograms are partially or completely reflected, vertically or horizontally, some with chromatic replacement.

The aspect ratio is 3:4. The palettes are predominantly based on found textile patterns.

Press 's' to save a png image. Press 'e' to redraw and export a 4K png image. Note that drawing and physical simulation takes some time.

For interactive use, press 't' to tilt the board and 'c' to clear the board.

Written in p5.js with 2D physical simulation using Matter.js. Developed in and optimized for Chrome.

metadata.name: NESTED IDENTITIES #164
metadata.description:
Nested identities redact fingerprints but deeper meaning can still be found.

Nested identifies refers to the idea that a person may have multiple identities that are interconnected and interdependent. These identities may be related to a person's cultural background, ethnicity, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, social class, profession, and other factors. It is possible that a person may want to conceal or redact certain aspects of their identity in order to protect their privacy or to avoid discrimination or persecution. However, even if certain details about a person's identity are hidden or redacted, it may still be possible to infer deeper meaning or understand more about their experiences and perspectives based on the context in which they express themselves and the information that is available.


The concept of nested identities highlights the complexity and multifaceted nature of a person's identity, and how different aspects of identity can intersect and influence each other. It is important to recognize and respect the diversity of identities that people may hold, and to be mindful of the ways in which power dynamics and social context can shape how people present and express their identities. It is also important to recognize that people's identities may evolve and change over time, and that everyone has the right to self-identify and to define their own identity on their own terms.

Press p to download a high quality export.

metadata.name: I AM UNFOLDING #124
metadata.description:
In the past, I was but fragments
Rough and jagged
Indefinitely, I weathered and grew
A sculpture formed, unstructured

In the present, I am the precipice
A grandiose monolith
My angles sharp, my lines precise
A work of art, restructured

The future looms before
A blank formlessness yet to be
My function undefined
In perpetuity, unfolding

-----------------------------------------

Best efforts have been made to optimize this project; however, for best performance, a machine with a dedicated GPU is recommended. Viewing the project in live mode is also recommended.

S - export a high resolution image.
P - pause the animation.
